        </div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0294-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0294-fn-0001">1</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Pio means the commissioners letter of 22 Sept. 1784. That letter has not been found, but for a record of its dispatch, see the commissioners <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0207" class="document">9 Sept.</a> letter to the Baron von Thulemeier, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0207&amp;expandNote=ADMS-06-16-02-0207-fn-0003#ADMS-06-16-02-0207-fn-0003" class="document">note 3</a>, above. Pio acknowledged receiving the commissioners letter in his reply of 26 Sept. (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;The Papers of Thomas Jefferson,&lt;/i&gt; ed. Julian P. Boyd, Charles T. Cullen, John Catanzariti, Barbara B. Oberg, and others, Princeton, 1950. ]">Jefferson, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Papers,</span></span> 7:424).</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0294-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0294-fn-0002">2</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">The enclosure has not been found.</p>

